config.clinical_question: Compare the effectiveness of letrozole+palbociclib with letrozole+ribociclib for the first line treatment of metastatic ER positive breast cancer.

confounders.name: age
confounders.description: Patient age in years at initiation of first‑line therapy

confounders.name: ecog_performance_status
confounders.description: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group performance status score

confounders.name: menopausal_status
confounders.description: Menopausal status at treatment start (relevant for aromatase‑inhibitor eligibility)

confounders.name: site_of_metastasis
confounders.description: Predominant anatomic site(s) of metastatic disease

confounders.name: baseline_liver_function
confounders.description: Serum total bilirubin (mg/dL) measured within 14 days before therapy

confounders.name: cardiovascular_comorbidity
categories: moderate (e.g., prior MI, heart failure NYHA I‑II)
severe (e.g., NYHA III‑IV, recent coronary event)
confounders.description: Severity of pre‑existing cardiovascular disease, influencing CDK4/6 inhibitor selection

confounders.name: prior_adjuvant_or_neoadjuvant_therapy
confounders.description: History of systemic therapy before metastatic diagnosis

confounders.name: ki67_index
confounders.description: Baseline tumor Ki‑67 proliferation index expressed as a percentage

confounders.name: her2_status
confounders.description: Immunohistochemistry/ISH result for HER2; HER2‑positive disease may alter treatment choice

confounders.name: insurance_coverage
confounders.description: Type of health insurance, which can affect access to specific CDK4/6 inhibitors and supportive care
